/Rect [122.913 539.367 486.903 745.353]
/Subtype /Widget
/T (tooltip zref@1)
/TU (The figure illustrates two main components: a Generator and a Discriminator. The Generator receives random noise as input and produces data samples. These generated samples and real data samples serve as inputs for the Discriminator, which then classifies them. The two components are in a feedback loop, with the Generator trying to produce data that the Discriminator can't distinguish from real and the Discriminator aiming to better distinguish between real and generated data.)
/Type /Annot
>>
