/Subtype /Widget
/T (tooltip zref@2)
/TU (Diagram illustrating the architecture of a Variational Autoencoder \(VAE\). The VAE is divided into two main parts: the Encoder and the Decoder. The Encoder receives input data and maps it to a latent space. The latent representation is then passed to the Decoder, which attempts to reconstruct the original input data. The architecture emphasises the probabilistic nature of the encoding and decoding processes, aiming to balance data compression in the latent space and accurate reconstruction.)
/Type /Annot
>>
